	NASUAD recommends that HHS include state directors on aging and disabilities in this collaboration, as well as state long-term care directors.</p>
<p>On behalf of NASUAD, I thank you for the opportunity to comment on the Draft National Plan to Address Alzheimer's Disease. We look forward to continuing to work with HHS to develop an approach that seeks to achieve the vision of a nation free of the disease, while maintaining the dignity and independence of older adults, individuals with disabilities, their families, and their caregivers. Please do not hesitate to contact me, or Lindsey Copeland, NASUAD's Director of Policy and Legislative Affairs to further discuss any of these issues.</p>
<p>Sincerely,</p>
<p>Martha A. Roherty<br />
	Executive Director</p>
